Both deliverables are emitted in the bundle directory and validate against the schema.

**Headline finding:** the only material treatment effect on `objective_response` in this 50,000-patient AML cohort is from `treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine`, and it is essentially confined to one four-predicate subgroup:

> `npm1_mutation == 1` **AND** `unfit_for_intensive == 1` **AND** `tp53_mutation == 0` **AND** `complex_karyotype == 0`

In that subgroup (n = 4,531 / ~9% of the cohort), response is **78.6% on ven/aza vs 15.8% off** (+62.8 pp; adjusted logit coefficient +3.04). Outside the subgroup the average treatment effect is ≈ 0 (16.4% vs 16.7%). Each of the four predicates is independently load-bearing — dropping any one collapses the effect.

Secondary findings: 7+3 numerically harms complex_karyotype patients (−2.3 pp, p = 0.0015); enasidenib has a small sex-modified effect (positive in females, negative in males, p = 2e-04). The expected FLT3- and IDH-targeted-therapy benefits in their respective mutation carriers were not present (midostaurin/gilteritinib in FLT3+, ivosidenib/enasidenib in IDH1/IDH2+ all null or numerically inverse). Outputs:

- `transcript.json` — 25 iterations, 51 hypotheses, 49 analyses
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative synthesis
